  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone has deleted or removed you from their contacts on **LINE** can be challenging, as the app doesn't provide explicit notifications or alerts for such actions. However, there are several indicators you can look for that may suggest you have been removed:\n\n1. **Profile Information Changes:**\n   - **Profile Picture:** If the person's profile photo disappears or changes to a default image, it might indicate they have removed you or adjusted their privacy settings.\n   - **Status Message:** Absence of their status message or a sudden change could be a sign.\n\n2. **Last Seen and Online Status:**\n   - If you previously could see their \"Last Seen\" or \"Online\" status and suddenly can't, they might have deleted you or changed their privacy settings to restrict this information.\n\n3. **Message Indicators:**\n   - **Sent Messages:** Messages you send may only show one check mark (message sent) instead of two (delivered) or blue check marks (read). This could suggest that the person has deleted you or is no longer reachable via LINE.\n   - **No Replies:** If your messages go unanswered consistently over a period, it might indicate you've been removed, though it could also mean the person is simply not active.\n\n4. **Unexpected Behavior When Searching:**\n   - If you try to search for the person's profile and it doesn't appear, they might have deleted their LINE account or blocked you.\n\n5. **Unable to Make Voice or Video Calls:**\n   - If your attempts to call them via LINE fail or you encounter errors, it's possible you've been removed or blocked.\n\n6. **Group Chats:**\n   - If you share a group chat with the person and notice that you're no longer connected or see changes in your interaction within the group, it could suggest a removal.\n\n7. **Notifications:**\n   - Lack of notifications from them, especially if you used to receive regular updates, can be another subtle hint.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Privacy Settings:** LINE offers various privacy settings. The person may have adjusted their settings to limit who can see their information without necessarily deleting or blocking you.\n  \n- **Temporary Issues:** Sometimes, technical glitches or server issues can cause temporary disruptions in visibility or communication.\n\n- **Respect Privacy:** If you suspect someone has removed you, it's important to respect their decision and privacy. Avoid attempting to circumvent their privacy settings or contacting them through alternative means if they prefer not to engage.\n\n**Steps to Verify:**\n\n1. **Check Your Contacts:**\n   - Go to your contact list and search for the person. If their profile doesn't appear, they might have removed you.\n\n2. **Attempt to Send a Message:**\n   - Try sending a message. If it consistently shows as \"sent\" but not \"delivered,\" this could indicate removal or blocking.\n\n3. **Search Their Profile Online:**\n   - Sometimes, searching their LINE ID or connected social media profiles can provide clues about their LINE status.\n\n4. **Use Another Account:**\n   - If appropriate, you might use another LINE account to check if the person is still active on LINE. However, ensure you respect their privacy and use ethical practices.\n\nRemember, these indicators are not foolproof. The most accurate way to confirm would be through direct communication, respecting the other person's boundaries and privacy.",
